OL,3,CFour-day weeks and driving limits: How
OL,4,Cthe world adapting during Iran oil
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FQatar's energy minister said two of
OL,8,Fthe LNG site's 14 trains - the term
OL,9,Ffor large industrial processing units
OL,10,F- had been damaged and estimated it
OL,11,Fcould take up to five years for them
OL,12,Fto be repaired.
OL,14,FITV News looks at how the world is
OL,15,Freacting to the energy crisis.
OL,17,FAsia has been the hardest hit by
OL,18,Fshortages, with the majority of oil
OL,19,Fand liquefied natural gas passing
OL,20,Fthrough the Strait of Hormuz destined
OL,21,Ffor the region.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
