OL,3,CFour-day weeks and driving limits: How
OL,4,Cthe world adapting during Iran oil
OL,5,Ccrisis
OL,7,FRural groups such as farmers and
OL,8,Ffishermen staged a protest against
OL,9,Frising fuel prices in Quezon City, the
OL,10,FPhilippines, March 10, calling on the
OL,11,Fgovernment to intervene.
OL,13,FThis week President Ferdinand Marcos
OL,14,FJr ordered the release of 21.47
OL,15,Fbillion Philippine Pesos (about
OL,16,F#268.06 million) to cushion the
OL,17,Fcountry against surging fuel prices
OL,18,Fand sustain infrastructure projects.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/19
